            <EntitySourceOfInformation EntitySourceOfInformationId="2547" SortOrder="15">
                <FooterDetails>
                    <Email/>
                    <Footer/>
                    <WebAddress>https://www.fca.gov/about/history/historyFCA_FCS.html</WebAddress>
                </FooterDetails>
                <Header>History</Header>
                <Paragraph>For centuries, North American farmers have sought reliable sources of credit to acquire land and to develop and expand farms. Their need to access long-term, fixed-rate credit has continued to the present. While 19th-century commercial banks made long-term credit available at reasonable rates to businessmen and industrial capitalists, they provided less of the same service to farmers. Presidents Theodore Roosevelt, William Howard Taft, and Woodrow Wilson saw the problem and sought solutions. To learn what they did to help 20th-century American farmers, visit the "History of FCA" Web page.</Paragraph>
            </EntitySourceOfInformation>
